                   measurements lacked a seasonal signal. However,
                   bottle incubations indicate that August nitrate
                   uptake was reduced by more than an order of magnitude
                   relative to the May values. It remains inconclusive
                   whether the new production was limited by an
                   unidentified factor other than NO3- supply in late
                   summer, or the uptake was underestimated by the
                   incubation method.},
