                   between 5\textdegree{}N and 5\textdegree{}S, it was
                   1.9 mmol m-2 d-1. The total supply of nitrate was
                   larger than the concurrently measured incorporation
                   of nitrate into particles but was comparable to the
                   integrated local rate of nitrate disappearance. The
                   discrepancy between new production estimated from
                   physical supply or from nitrate disappearance and
                   that estimated from nitrate incorporation into
                   particles suggests that uptake by small cells ({$<$}
                   1 {$\mathrm{\mu}$}m), dissolved organic N, or both
                   play an important role in the equatorial region.},
